
ClarityPath AI PRD

 Product Name

ClarityPath AI – Personalized AI learning path recommender.

 Problem Statement
Learners struggle to decide what to learn next due to the overwhelming number of courses, unclear career goals, and lack of personalized guidance. This leads to wasted time, confusion, poor skill alignment, and low learning completion rates.

Goal
-Provide learners with a clear, AI-generated learning roadmap based on their goals, skills, and background.

-Help learners stay consistent and achieve career or personal development objectives.

Target Users

Students

Fresh graduates

Self-learners

Tech career switchers

Working professionals

Companies training staff

Key Features

1. User Input – Collect learning goals, skills, background, learning style, time availability.

2. Skill Assessment – AI evaluates current skill level and gaps.

3. Learning Path Generation – AI generates structured step-by-step roadmap.

4. Course/Resource Recommendations – Suggests courses, YouTube playlists, tools, or exercises.

5. Weekly Task Planner – Breaks roadmap into weekly tasks.

6. Progress Tracking – Users can mark completed/in-progress tasks.

7. Save/Export Options – PDF or Notion export for later reference.

 AI Use

Recommendation system (suggest courses & tasks)

User profiling (skills, goals, preferences)

Learning path generation

Competitors / Market Gap

1.Coursera / Udemy: offers course recommendations but there's no structured, step-by-step roadmap personalized by AI

2. Skillshare:topic suggestions but no goal-aligned learning paths

3.EdApp / Degreed: corporate learning & analytics. It is complex, not beginner-friendly

4.Pathrise / CareerFoundry:Mentor-guided paths but human-led, not automated by AI

Opportunity: ClarityPath AI fills the gap for fast, personalized, structured, and automated learning path
 
User Stories & Acceptance Criteria

User Story 1:
As a student, I want to input my learning goals and current skills so the AI can generate a personalized roadmap.

Acceptance Criteria:

User can enter goals and skills through a form or text input

AI responds with a structured learning path

User Story 2:
As a self-learner, I want weekly tasks from my learning path so I can track progress.

Acceptance Criteria:

AI breaks roadmap into weekly tasks

User can mark tasks as completed or in-progress

User Story 3:
As a working professional, I want course and resource suggestions aligned with my goals.

Acceptance Criteria:

AI recommends courses, videos, and exercises relevant to user goals

Recommendations include level and estimated time

User Story 4:
As a tech career switcher, I want to save/export my learning path so I can follow it offline or in another tool.

Acceptance Criteria:

User can download roadmap as PDF or export to Notion

User Story 5:
As a company training staff, I want to generate learning paths for multiple employees.

Acceptance Criteria:

Admin can input multiple profiles

AI generates separate learning paths for each profile

 Success Metrics

Users can generate a personalized path in less than 5 minutes

Learning path contains relevant, achievable tasks

Users report improved clarity on “what to learn next”

Workflow / User Flow

1. User enters goals and background info

2. AI analyzes input and evaluates skills

3. AI generates personalized learning path

4. User reviews roadmap and weekly tasks

5. User tracks progress and saves/export path

 Feasibility / Cost

Prototype: Figma, Notion- minimal cost

AI recommendation: free-tier OpenAI API

Full deployment: budget for API usage and hosting

Future Scope (Optional Features)

Integration with Udemy/Coursera APIs

AI quizzes for skill verification

Job-role recommendations based on skills

Mobile/web app version

